#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn17.36:0.2"
msgid "4. Catutthavagga "
msgstr "4. The Fourth Chapter "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
#. VAR: 36. Pañcarathasatasutta → ratha (pts1-2)
msgctxt "sn17.36:0.3"
msgid "36. Pañcarathasatasutta "
msgstr "36. Five Hundred Carts "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli2.242, sc1
msgctxt "sn17.36:1.1"
msgid "Rājagahe viharati veḷuvane kalandakanivāpe. "
msgstr "Near Rājagaha, in the Bamboo Grove, the squirrels’ feeding ground. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
# NOTE: https://discourse.suttacentral.net/t/on-dishes-of-meals-kings-and-offerings/3970
msgctxt "sn17.36:1.2"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena devadattassa ajātasattukumāro pañcahi rathasatehi sāyaṃ pātaṃ upaṭṭhānaṃ gacchati, pañca ca thālipākasatāni bhattābhihāro abhiharīyati. "
msgstr "Now at that time Prince Ajātasattu was going with five hundred carts in the morning and the evening to attend on Devadatta, presenting him with an offering of five hundred servings of food. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn17.36:1.3"
msgid "Atha kho sambahulā bhikkhū yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu. Ekamantaṃ nisinnā kho te bhikkhū bhagavantaṃ etadavocuṃ: "
msgstr "Then several mendicants went up to the Buddha, bowed, sat down to one side, and said to him, "

msgctxt "sn17.36:1.4"
msgid "“devadattassa, bhante, ajātasattukumāro pañcahi rathasatehi sāyaṃ pātaṃ upaṭṭhānaṃ gacchati, pañca ca thālipākasatāni bhattābhihāro abhiharīyatī”ti. "
msgstr "“Sir, Prince Ajātasattu is going with five hundred carts in the morning and the evening to attend on Devadatta, presenting him with an offering of five hundred servings of food.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn17.36:1.5"
msgid "“Mā, bhikkhave, devadattassa lābhasakkārasilokaṃ pihayittha. "
msgstr "“Mendicants, don’t envy Devadatta’s possessions, honor, and popularity. "

msgctxt "sn17.36:1.6"
msgid "Yāvakīvañca, bhikkhave, devadattassa ajātasattukumāro pañcahi rathasatehi sāyaṃ pātaṃ upaṭṭhānaṃ gamissati, pañca ca thālipākasatāni bhattābhihāro āharīyissati, hāniyeva, bhikkhave, devadattassa pāṭikaṅkhā kusalesu dhammesu, no vuddhi. "
msgstr "As long as Prince Ajātasattu goes with five hundred carts in the morning and the evening to attend on Devadatta, presenting him with an offering of five hundred servings of food, Devadatta can expect decline, not growth, in skillful qualities. "

# NOTE: See BB’s note on this. He follows the comm. The simile is found in one of the parallels for this, EA 23.7: 如取惡狗 鼻壞之，倍復凶惡. Here, 壞 probably stands for √bhind and there is no term for pitta. nevertheless, i translate literally, reading nasaya as ablative.
#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "sn17.36:2.1"
msgid "Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, caṇḍassa kukkurassa nāsāya pittaṃ bhindeyyuṃ, evañhi so, bhikkhave, kukkuro bhiyyoso mattāya caṇḍataro assa; "
msgstr "If bile were to burst from a wild dog’s nose, it would become even wilder. "

msgctxt "sn17.36:2.2"
msgid "evameva, bhikkhave, yāvakīvañca devadattassa ajātasattukumāro pañcahi rathasatehi sāyaṃ pātaṃ upaṭṭhānaṃ gamissati, pañca ca thālipākasatāni bhattābhihāro āharīyissati, hāniyeva, bhikkhave, devadattassa pāṭikaṅkhā kusalesu dhammesu, no vuddhi. "
msgstr "In the same way, as long as Prince Ajātasattu goes with five hundred carts in the morning and the evening to attend on Devadatta, presenting him with an offering of five hundred servings of food, Devadatta can expect decline, not growth, in skillful qualities. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn17.36:2.3"
msgid "Evaṃ dāruṇo kho, bhikkhave, lābhasakkārasiloko … pe … "
msgstr "So brutal are possessions, honor, and popularity. …” "

msgctxt "sn17.36:2.4"
msgid "evañhi vo, bhikkhave, sikkhitabban”ti. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn17.36:2.5"
msgid "Chaṭṭhaṃ. "
msgstr ""

